# Cursor documents map

Download descriptions from files IF you need to understand the work:
1. Architecture (Technical solutions):
   - [Fixtures Structure](../docs/Architecture/FixturesStructure.md)

2. Features:
   - [Lexer](../docs/Feature/Lexer.md)
   - [Parser](../docs/Feature/Parser.md)
   - [Showing of problematic position](../docs/Feature/ShowingProblematicPosition.md)
   - [Specification Cover Fixtures Structure](../docs/Feature/SpecificationCoverFixtures.md)

When updating functionality or when explicitly requested, update the corresponding documentation files.
   - First, business logic/steps with minimal technical details, then additional logic with minimal technical details,
     and finally, technical details (architecture, paths, settings, commands, etc.).
   - Update without blocks with the latest changes, as if you were doing it from scratch for complete documentation.
   - Keep documentation of Architecture (Technical solutions) in directory [Architecture](../docs/Architecture) and add path to such file
     in section `1. Architecture (Technical solutions):` above like others.
   - Keep documentation of Features in directory [Feature](../docs/Feature) and add path to such file in section `2. Features:` above like others.

When creating new documentation files:
   - After creating a new Architecture documentation file, add a link to it in section `1. Architecture (Technical solutions):` above.
     Format: `- [Description](../docs/Architecture/[FileName].md)` (Markdown links format).
   - After creating a new Feature documentation file, add a link to it in section `2. Features:` above.
     Format: `- [Description](../docs/Feature/[FileName].md)` (Markdown links format).
   - Use paths relative to THIS file (`.cursor/rules/doc.mdc`) for all links in this document.
     Since this file is located in `.cursor/rules/`, links to the documentation in `.cursor/docs/` must start with `../docs/`
     (e.g. `../docs/Feature/Parser.md` or `../docs/Architecture/Foo.md`).
   - Keep entries in alphabetical order by description for better organization.

IMPORTANT: You MUST NOT create links from user's documents to `.cursor` rules! Keep them totally separated.
           But you can use vice versa (link from your documentation to user's documentation)
           where it makes sense and does not lead to excessive use of context.

All documentation have to be written on English.
